<p>A paragraph (from the Greek paragraphos, "to write beside" or "written beside") is a self-contained unit of a discourse in writing dealing with a particular <em>point or idea</em>. A paragraph consists of one or more sentences. Though not required by the <strong>syntax of any language</strong>, paragraphs are <a href="#">usually an expected</a> part of formal writing, used to organize longer prose.</p>